<HEAD>List of Week's TV Shows Ratings</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Nielsens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the prime-time television ratings as
compiled by the A.C. Nielsen Co. for the week of Feb. 20-26. Top 20
listings include the week's ranking, with full season-to-date
ranking in parentheses, rating for the week, and total homes.
   An ``X'' in parentheses denotes one-time-only presentation. A
rating measures the percentage of the nation's 90.4 million TV homes.
   1. (1) ``The Cosby Show,'' NBC, 27.2 rating, 24.5 million homes.
   2. (3) ``A Different World,'' NBC, 24.9, 22.5 million homes.
   3. (2) ``Roseanne,'' ABC, 24.2, 21.8 million homes.
   4. (5) ``60 Minutes,'' CBS, 23.8, 21.5 million homes.
   5. (4) ``Cheers,'', NBC, 23.3, 21.0 million homes.
   6. (8) ``Murder, She Wrote,'' CBS, 22.8, 20.6 million homes.
   7. (6) ``Golden Girls,'' NBC, 22.5, 20.3 million homes.
   8. (7) ``Who's The Boss?'' ABC, 21.9, 19.7 million homes.
   9. (20) ``Naked Lie,'' _ ``CBS Sunday Night Movie,'' 21.2, 19.1
million homes.
   10. (11) ``Dear John,'' NBC, 19.8, 17.9 million homes.
   11. (9) ``Empty Nest,'' NBC, 19.7, 17.8 million homes.
   12. (12) ``L.A. Law,'' NBC, 19.6, 17.7 million homes.
   13. (15) ``In the Heat of the Night,'' NBC, 19.2, 17.3 million
homes.
   14. (13) ``Matlock,'' NBC, 18.6, 16.8 million homes.
   15. (17) ``Hunter,'' NBC, 18.5, 16.7 million homes.
   16. (14) ``ALF,'' NBC, 18.4, 16.6 million homes.
   17. (28) ``Dallas,'' CBS, 17.9, 16.2 million homes.
   18. (17) ``Unsolved Mysteries,'' NBC, 17.5, 15.8 million homes.
   18. (29) ``Full House,'' ABC, 17.5, 15.8 million homes.
