<FIRST>r i PM-MoneyorTime     03-01 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Money or Time,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>Judge Orders Drug Smuggler To Hand Over Millions or Face An Extra
10 Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>READING, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge gave a convicted drug smuggler
this choice: hand over nearly $2.95 million or have another decade
added to your 8{-year jail sentence.
   Ronald French, 37, did not say in court Tuesday whether he would
pay up _ the law gives him a year to come up with the cash _ or
serve the extra time.
   The seizure, ordered by Judge John Murchie at Reading Crown
Court, was the heaviest so far under Britain's new Drug Trafficking
Act, which allows courts to confiscate the proceeds of illegal drug
smuggling.
   The court convicted French in August of plotting to smuggle 790
pounds of marijuana into Britain with the help of an Air France
employee.
   His sentencing was postponed until Tuesday for an inquiry into
his assets.
   During a hearing on the assets, Murchie was told of French's
various aliases, his 21 bank accounts in Switzerland and Spain and
his companies or other interests in Luxembourg, Panama, Liberia and
South Africa.
   The judge said Tuesday that he assessed French's assets from drug
smuggling at $4.3 million, with $2.95 million recoverable.
</TEXT>
