<SECOND>PM-Chicago Mayors-List,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Daley Would Become City's Sixth Mayor in 13 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard M. Daley, who won the Democratic mayoral
primary, would become Chicago's sixth mayor in the last 13 years if
he wins the general election April 4. The others are:
   _ His father, Richard J. Daley, elected in 1955, served for 21
years until his death in December 1976.
   _ Michael Bilandic, acting mayor following Daley's death in 1976;
elected in 1977 to fill the final two years of Daley's four-year
term; defeated in the 1979 Democratic primary by Jane Byrne.
   _ Byrne, elected in the 1979 general election, lost in the 1983
Democratic primary in a three-way race with the younger Daley and
Harold Washington.
   _ Washington, elected in 1983 as the city's first black mayor;
re-elected in 1987; died Nov. 25, 1987, seven months into his second
term.
   _ Eugene Sawyer, named acting mayor by City Council on Dec. 2,
1987; defeated in Tuesday's Democratic primary by Daley.
</TEXT>
