<HEAD>Snow in Rockies And Plains, Heavy Rain In Florida</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell over the Rockies and the Plains today, and up to 7
inches of rain drenched southern Florida.
   Advisories for snow along with strong winds were posted for the
mountains of northwest Montana, the upper Yellowstone Valley in
south-central Montana and the Idaho Panhandle.
   A freezing rain advisory was posted this morning at the Pikes
Peak-Palmer Divide in east-central Colorado, and a winter storm
watch was posted for tonight and Thursday in the northern mountains
of Idaho.
   In the Southeast, afternoon and evening thunderstorms produced as
much as 7 inches of rain near Fort Lauderdale, Fla., and more than 3
inches at Davie, Fla.
   Snow was falling today in parts of Washington state, Idaho,
Montana, Wyoming, South Dakota, Nebraska, Kansas, Colorado and
Michigan.
   Rain was scattered from western Texas across east-central Texas
and central Louisiana into central Mississippi.
   The nation's high temperature Tuesday was 87 degrees at Coolidge,
Ariz., El Centro, Calif., Imperial, Calif., La Jitas, Texas,
Presidio, Texas, and Thermal, Calif.
   Today's forecast called for snowshowers extending from northern
New England across northeast New York and along the lower Great
Lakes, in upper Michigan, from Iowa across southern Minnesota, South
Dakota, northern Nebraska, Montana and western Washington. Snow was
to change to rain in eastern Washington.
   Predicted highs: single numbers and teens from upper Michigan
across northern Wisconsin, Minnesota, the Dakotas, Montana and
northern Wyoming; 20s and 30s from New England across the remainder
of the Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, the central Mississippi Valley,
the central Plains and the northern Plateau; 40s and 50s from
southeast New York to northern Florida, the Tennessee Valley, the
northern part of the central Gulf of Mexico states, the lower
Mississippi Valley, from Oklahoma across northeast Texas, the lower
half of the Rockies, the Great Basin and the northern Pacific Coast;
60s in the Florida Panhandle, southeast Louisiana, southwest Texas,
New Mexico, the southern two-thirds of the California coast and the
lower Texas Gulf Coast; 70s and low 80s through the desert Southwest
and the Florida peninsula.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 20
degrees below zero at Warroad, Minn., to 73 at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 44 partly cloudy; Boston 30 fair; Buffalo 21
windy; Charleston, S.C., 45 cloudy; Cincinnati 21 fair; Cleveland 23
partly cloudy; Detroit 20 windy; Miami 70 partly cloudy; New York 32
foggy; Philadelphia 30 foggy; Pittsburgh 25 fair; Portland, Maine 18
fair; Washington 29 foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck -4 cloudy; Chicago 14 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
45 cloudy; Denver 20 freezing drizzle; Des Moines 13 fair;
Indianapolis 19 fair; Kansas City 23 partly cloudy; Nashville 34
partly cloudy; New Orleans 56 cloudy; St. Louis 23 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 39 fair; Las Vegas 55 fair; Los Angeles 52
partly cloudy; Phoenix 61 partly cloudy; Salt Lake City 31 fair; San
Diego 55 partly cloudy; San Francisco 48 showers; Seattle 35 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 25 snow; Toronto 21 snow.
