Stripes and he will be taking out another ad saying that the sand,
photograph and letteris ad that he pl of authenticity are no longer available
for
sale,'' Rothfork said.
   Wills spent a year on the tiny Japanese island before being
transferred to Guam last year.
   He took with him a package of sand he scooped up on Invasion
Beach, Rothfork said, and when he advertised sales of such sand,
military officials in Guam investigated.
   ``At this point, the matter is closed,'' Rothfork said.
   The 3,500-yard beach is where 30,000 U.S. Marines came ashore on
