<HEAD>`Big Daddy Kane' Arrested After Bus Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESTPORT, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rap musician Antonio M. Hardy, better known
as ``Big Daddy Kane,'' was arrested after he shot a man in the arm
while traveling aboard a chartered bus, police said Wednesday.
   Hardy, 20, of the borough of Brooklyn, was on his way from New
York City to an amusement park in North Hudson on Tuesday, where he
planned to make a music video. Sometime during the trip, he fired a
gun, state police said. The bullet ricocheted off a bus window and
struck 21-year-old Adrian M. White, said Sgt. Mike Downs.
   White, of Freeport, was treated at a hospital and released.
   Hardy pleaded guilty Tuesday afternoon in Schroon Lake Town Court
to third-degree assault and fourth-degree criminal possession of a
weapon.
