   Q. You said Sunday you've never broken a pledge in your life.
Does this include wedding vows?
   A. As a matter of fact, I have broken wedding vows.
   I think I am probably not alone in that connection.
   Q. Senator, have you considered waiving the privacy provisions of
the FBI report so that portions of it could be released to the
public?
   A. It's not up to me to waive the privacy provisions.
   The privacy provisions, I think, apply essentially to the people
who were interviewed, and I don't think it's within the purview of
my power to waive anything.
   I have not seen the FBI report, I don't know what's in it and I
can't comment on _ really on _ or express any attitude on what
should be done with the report in terms of revealing sections of it
or all of it or a redacted version of it.
   I simply have no way of making a judgment.
