<FIRST>r i AM-Canada-SpaceAgency     03-01 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Canada-Space Agency,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Canada Announces Space Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTREAL (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government announced on Wednesday that it
would form its own national space agency.
   Cabinet Minister Harvie Andre, minister of state for science and
technology, said the purpose of the agency was to coordinate
Canada's efforts in domestic and international space programs,
currently divided among several federal departments.
   Andre said the agency wuld be headquartered in Montreal and have
about 352 employees. He said it would direct expenditures of almost
$3 billion until the end of the century, with a mandate to spread
the contracts throughout the country.
   The agency will be set up immediately and its president will be
Larkin Kerwin, who now holds the same position with the National
Research Council in Ottawa, Andre said.
</TEXT>
