<TEXT>
   A task force of aviation industry and
government safety experts has proposed an $800 million overhaul of
the nation's older Boeing 747s, 737s and 727s to avert safety
problems.
   The group, set up by the Air Transport Association, which
represents major U.S. airlines, asked the Federal Aviation
Administration to issue a massive ``airworthiness directive'' in a
proposal released Tuesday. The directive would require modifications
recommended in Boeing Co. service bulletins.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. trade deficit worsened in the final
three months of the year, climbing to $32 billion, reflecting record
high levels of both exports and imports, the government said.
   The Commerce Department report released Tuesday said the deficit
from October through December swelled by 10 percent from a
third-quarter deficit of $29.17 billion. Economists expressed fear
that the deficit's recent improvement has stalled and will restrain
economic growth this year.
