<HEAD>Oldsmobile Extends Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp.'s Oldsmobile division is
extending its free-gasoline and cash-back incentive programs for
buyers of 1989 Eighty-Eight Royale models, the company said
Wednesday.
   The free gasoline program gives Eighty-Eight Royale buyers Exxon,
Amoco or Chevron credit cards with a value of $648, the EPA's
estimated annual fuel cost for the cars.
   The other program involves cash incentives for buyers of several
models, including rebates of $1,500 for Toronado and Trofeo, $1,000
for Ninety-Eight Regency models and Touring Sedans, $500 for Cutlass
Supreme models and Cutlass Calais models without Quad 4 engines,
$400 for Eighty-Eight Royale models and $300 for Cutlass Calais
models without Quad 4 engines.
   The programs, both scheduled to expire Wednesday, were extended
indefinitely, the company said.
  
