<HEAD>Smith Steps Down As American Express Bank CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Express Co. said Wednesday that Robert
F. Smith will retire as chairman and chief executive officer of its
banking subsidiary by July 1.
   A replacement has not yet been named.
   Smith, 56, joined American Express as senior president and
treasurer in February 1981 and was elected vice chairman of American
Express Bank Ltd. and a member of its board of directors six months
later.
   He became the bank's president and chief operating officer in
1983, and has held the position of chairman and chief executive
officer since January 1985.
