<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     03-01 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Energy Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The energy futures market ended mixed in moderate
trading Wednesday, with crude oil and wholesale home heating oil
prices rising and unleaded gasoline falling slightly.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the April contract for West
Texas Intermediate, the benchmark U.S. crude, settled 13 cents
higher at $18.28 a barrel, after gaining a penny on Tuesday. Other
contract months increased.
   Among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange, heating
oil for April delivery settled at 50.49 cents a gallon, up 0.30
cent. The contract had fallen 0.20 cent Tuesday.
   April unleaded gasoline, which rose 0.14 cent in the previous
session, fell 0.01 cent to 51.56 cents a gallon. Other contract
months were mostly lower.
   William Byers, an energy analyst with Bear, Stearns &amp; Co.,
attributed Wednesday's market activity largely to the latest
American Petroleum Institute data released late Tuesday.
   The API report showed a small buildup of gasoline and oil
supplies and a decline in heating oil.
</TEXT>
