<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Woolworth     03-01 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Woolworth,0206</SECOND>
<HEAD>Retailer Reports Record Income</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   F.W. Woolworth Co. Wednesday said its profit rose
9.9 percent in the fourth quarter to a record level, and annual
income grew 14.7 percent, also to an all-time high.
   The New York-based retailer, which has extensive operations
overseas, said after-tax income totaled $144 million, or $2.23 a
share, on revenue of $2.55 billion in the quarter ended Jan. 28, up
from $131 million, or $2 a share, and $2.24 billion in the
corresponding quarter a year earlier.
   Woolworth earned $288 million, or $4.47 a share, and revenue
totaled $8.09 billion in the year ended Jan. 28. A year before, net
income came to $251 million, or $3.81 a share, and revenue was $7.18
billion.
   During the year, Woolworth opened or acquired 1,154 stores and
closed 214. Capital outlays in the year totaled a record amount,
$450 million, including $176 million for acquisitions.
   In addition to its Woolworth stores, the retailer owns more than
1,000 Foot Locker athletic shoe shops, more than 1,800 Kinney shoe
stores and numerous other apparel, drug and general merchandisers.
   Woolworth's international holdings include stores in Australia,
Canada, and West Germany.
